<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Cloud Share</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/</link><description>Recent content on Cloud Share</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Allowed Hosts &amp; Ports</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/network/requirements/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/network/requirements/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="sender-machine"&gt;Sender machine &lt;a href="#sender-machine" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The sender machine needs outbound access to the following hosts on port &lt;strong&gt;443 (HTTPS)&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
 &lt;thead&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Host&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Purpose&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/thead&gt;
 &lt;tbody&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;*.devtunnels.ms&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Dev Tunnel relay — all tunnel traffic&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;global.rel.tunnels.api.visualstudio.com&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Dev Tunnels management API&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;login.microsoftonline.com&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Microsoft OAuth (Microsoft account login)&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;login.live.com&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Microsoft personal account login&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;github.com&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;GitHub OAuth (GitHub account login)&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;aka.ms&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Microsoft shortlinks (DevTunnel CLI installer redirect)&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;cdn.jsdelivr.net&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Bootstrap 5, Bootstrap Icons, Alpine.js (sender web UI CDN)&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ℹ️ Info:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;*.devtunnels.ms&lt;/code&gt; is a wildcard — the tunnel URL is a unique subdomain generated per session (e.g. &lt;code&gt;abc123.devtunnels.ms&lt;/code&gt;). Your firewall rule must allow all subdomains.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Encryption Architecture</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/security/architecture/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/security/architecture/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="encryption-architecture"&gt;Encryption Architecture &lt;a href="#encryption-architecture" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;This page documents the complete security architecture of cloud-share, including every cryptographic operation performed on items in transit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="end-to-end-encryption-model"&gt;End-to-end encryption model &lt;a href="#end-to-end-encryption-model" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Cloud Share encrypts content at the application layer on the sender before it leaves the process memory. The Dev Tunnel and HTTPS add a second layer of transport encryption. The receiver decrypts at the application layer after downloading.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="mermaid"&gt;sequenceDiagram
 participant SP as Sender Process
 participant DT as Dev Tunnel / HTTPS
 participant RP as Receiver Process

 SP-&amp;gt;&amp;gt;SP: SHA-512(plaintext) → stored
 SP-&amp;gt;&amp;gt;SP: AES-256-GCM encrypt&amp;lt;br/&amp;gt;(key=HKDF-SHA256(secret), nonce=random 12B)
 SP-&amp;gt;&amp;gt;SP: Base64(nonce ‖ cipher ‖ tag)
 SP-&amp;gt;&amp;gt;DT: Send over HTTPS/TLS
 DT-&amp;gt;&amp;gt;RP: Encrypted payload
 RP-&amp;gt;&amp;gt;RP: Base64 decode
 RP-&amp;gt;&amp;gt;RP: AES-256-GCM decrypt
 RP-&amp;gt;&amp;gt;RP: SHA-512 verify
 RP-&amp;gt;&amp;gt;RP: ✅ Plaintext content delivered
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="key-derivation"&gt;Key derivation &lt;a href="#key-derivation" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="secret-generation"&gt;Secret generation &lt;a href="#secret-generation" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;On each sender start, a &lt;strong&gt;12-character alphanumeric secret&lt;/strong&gt; is generated using a cryptographically secure random number generator. It is:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Installation</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/getting-started/installation/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/getting-started/installation/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="installation"&gt;Installation &lt;a href="#installation" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Cloud Share consists of two .NET 10 global tools published to NuGet. Installation takes about two minutes on any platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="prerequisites"&gt;Prerequisites &lt;a href="#prerequisites" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="net-10-sdk"&gt;.NET 10 SDK &lt;a href="#net-10-sdk" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Both tools require the &lt;strong&gt;.NET 10 SDK or Runtime&lt;/strong&gt;. Download it from &lt;a href="https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download/dotnet/10.0" rel="external" target="_blank"&gt;dot.net&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Installation &amp; Authentication</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/troubleshooting/installation/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/troubleshooting/installation/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="devtunnels-cli-not-found"&gt;DevTunnels CLI not found &lt;a href="#devtunnels-cli-not-found" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Symptom:&lt;/strong&gt; The sender fails to start with an error like:&lt;/p&gt;



 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock "&gt;
 &lt;pre id="ac1053b" class="language- "&gt;
 &lt;code&gt;Error: &amp;#39;devtunnel&amp;#39; is not recognized as a command&lt;/code&gt;
 &lt;/pre&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;



 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock "&gt;
 &lt;pre id="c326154" class="language- "&gt;
 &lt;code&gt;DevTunnel CLI not found. Attempting auto-install...&lt;/code&gt;
 &lt;/pre&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cause:&lt;/strong&gt; The &lt;code&gt;devtunnel&lt;/code&gt; CLI is not in your &lt;code&gt;PATH&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Resolution:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cloud Share will attempt to install the DevTunnels CLI automatically. If auto-install fails or you prefer manual installation:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id="windows"&gt;Windows &lt;a href="#windows" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;


 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock "&gt;
 &lt;pre id="df6843c" class="language-powershell "&gt;
 &lt;code&gt;winget install Microsoft.devtunnel&lt;/code&gt;
 &lt;/pre&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h4 id="macos"&gt;macOS &lt;a href="#macos" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;


 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock "&gt;
 &lt;pre id="68ab8b5" class="language-bash "&gt;
 &lt;code&gt;brew install --cask devtunnel&lt;/code&gt;
 &lt;/pre&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h4 id="linux"&gt;Linux &lt;a href="#linux" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;


 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock "&gt;
 &lt;pre id="cf27951" class="language-bash "&gt;
 &lt;code&gt;curl -sL https://aka.ms/DevTunnelCliInstall | bash&lt;/code&gt;
 &lt;/pre&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After installation, open a &lt;strong&gt;new terminal window&lt;/strong&gt; (to pick up the updated PATH) and try again.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Sender CLI Reference</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/cli-reference/sender/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/cli-reference/sender/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="sender-cli-reference"&gt;Sender CLI Reference &lt;a href="#sender-cli-reference" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;cloud-share-sender&lt;/code&gt; is the NuGet global tool that starts the local web server, creates the Dev Tunnel, and manages the queue of items to be shared.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="synopsis"&gt;Synopsis &lt;a href="#synopsis" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;


 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock "&gt;
 &lt;pre id="f5a1049" class="language- "&gt;
 &lt;code&gt;cloud-share-sender [options]&lt;/code&gt;
 &lt;/pre&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="flags"&gt;Flags &lt;a href="#flags" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;table&gt;
 &lt;thead&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Flag&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Short&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Default&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Description&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/thead&gt;
 &lt;tbody&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;--port&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;-p&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;5000&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;The local port to listen on&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;--log&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;-l&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;warnings&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Log level: &lt;code&gt;verbose&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;warnings&lt;/code&gt;, or &lt;code&gt;errors&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;--reset&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Re-authenticate with DevTunnels (clears saved login)&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;--no-auto-open&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Do not open the web UI in the browser on startup&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;--help&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;-h&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Show help text&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;--version&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Show the tool version&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="flag-details"&gt;Flag details &lt;a href="#flag-details" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="--port---p"&gt;&lt;code&gt;--port&lt;/code&gt; / &lt;code&gt;-p&lt;/code&gt; &lt;a href="#--port---p" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Sets the local TCP port the sender&amp;rsquo;s HTTP server listens on. The Dev Tunnel proxies to this port.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Text Sharing</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/features/text-sharing/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/features/text-sharing/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="text-sharing"&gt;Text Sharing &lt;a href="#text-sharing" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Text sharing is the fastest way to send a snippet — a command, a password, a code block, or any plain text up to &lt;strong&gt;10 MB&lt;/strong&gt; — from one machine to another.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="sending-text"&gt;Sending text &lt;a href="#sending-text" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="in-the-sender-ui"&gt;In the sender UI &lt;a href="#in-the-sender-ui" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open the sender web UI (auto-opens at &lt;code&gt;http://localhost:5000&lt;/code&gt;, or re-open via browser)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Click the &lt;strong&gt;Text&lt;/strong&gt; tab&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📸 Screenshot needed:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;text-sharing-sender-tab.png&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;em&gt;Description: Sender web UI with the Text tab selected, showing the text area and Share button&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Connectivity &amp; Secret Issues</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/troubleshooting/connectivity/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/troubleshooting/connectivity/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="connection-refused--receiver-cannot-connect"&gt;Connection refused / receiver cannot connect &lt;a href="#connection-refused--receiver-cannot-connect" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Symptom:&lt;/strong&gt; The receiver shows:&lt;/p&gt;



 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock "&gt;
 &lt;pre id="6285705" class="language- "&gt;
 &lt;code&gt;Error: Connection refused&lt;/code&gt;
 &lt;/pre&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or the queue never loads and the status badge shows &lt;strong&gt;Disconnected&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cause:&lt;/strong&gt; One of several things:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The sender is not running&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The wrong tunnel URL was entered&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Dev Tunnel has expired (sender was stopped and restarted with a new URL)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A firewall is blocking &lt;code&gt;*.devtunnels.ms:443&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Resolution:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify the sender is running and shows a tunnel URL in its output&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirm the receiver is using the exact URL from the current sender session (URLs change on each restart)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Test connectivity: &lt;code&gt;curl -I https://&amp;lt;tunnel-url&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; — you should get a 200 or 401 response&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check your firewall allows outbound HTTPS to &lt;code&gt;*.devtunnels.ms:443&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you restarted the sender, start the receiver fresh with the new URL and secret:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>File Transfer</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/features/file-transfer/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/features/file-transfer/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="file-transfer"&gt;File Transfer &lt;a href="#file-transfer" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Cloud Share can transfer individual files up to &lt;strong&gt;100 MB&lt;/strong&gt; — encrypted in transit with AES-256-GCM and verified on arrival with SHA-512.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="uploading-a-file"&gt;Uploading a file &lt;a href="#uploading-a-file" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="in-the-sender-ui"&gt;In the sender UI &lt;a href="#in-the-sender-ui" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open the sender web UI (&lt;code&gt;http://localhost:5000&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Click the &lt;strong&gt;File&lt;/strong&gt; tab&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📸 Screenshot needed:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;file-transfer-sender-tab.png&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;em&gt;Description: Sender web UI with the File tab selected, showing the drag-and-drop zone&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start="3"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Either:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drag and drop&lt;/strong&gt; a file onto the drop zone&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Click &lt;strong&gt;Browse&lt;/strong&gt; (or the drop zone) to open a file picker&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📸 Screenshot needed:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;file-transfer-sender-dragdrop.png&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;em&gt;Description: File tab with a file being dragged onto the drop zone, showing the hover state&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Proxy Environments</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/network/proxy/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/network/proxy/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;If your network requires a proxy for outbound HTTPS, configure it via the standard .NET environment variables before starting either tool.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="configuration"&gt;Configuration &lt;a href="#configuration" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;


 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock "&gt;
 &lt;pre id="1a86c15" class="language-bash "&gt;
 &lt;code&gt;# Linux / macOS
export HTTPS_PROXY=http://proxy.corp.example.com:8080
cloud-share-sender

# Windows (PowerShell)
$env:HTTPS_PROXY = &amp;#34;http://proxy.corp.example.com:8080&amp;#34;
cloud-share-sender&lt;/code&gt;
 &lt;/pre&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;devtunnel&lt;/code&gt; CLI respects system proxy settings on Windows. On Linux/macOS, set &lt;code&gt;HTTPS_PROXY&lt;/code&gt; before running &lt;code&gt;cloud-share-sender&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;cloud-share-receiver&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="authenticated-proxies"&gt;Authenticated proxies &lt;a href="#authenticated-proxies" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;If your proxy requires credentials, include them in the URL:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Quick Start</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/getting-started/quickstart/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/getting-started/quickstart/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="quick-start"&gt;Quick Start &lt;a href="#quick-start" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;This guide walks you through your very first cloud-share transfer — from starting the sender to receiving and verifying a file on another machine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ℹ️ Info:&lt;/strong&gt; You need two machines (or two terminal windows) to complete this walkthrough: one acting as the &lt;strong&gt;sender&lt;/strong&gt; and one as the &lt;strong&gt;receiver&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="step-1--start-the-sender"&gt;Step 1 — Start the sender &lt;a href="#step-1--start-the-sender" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;On the &lt;strong&gt;sending machine&lt;/strong&gt;, open a terminal and run:&lt;/p&gt;



 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock "&gt;
 &lt;pre id="a06bff3" class="language-bash "&gt;
 &lt;code&gt;cloud-share-sender&lt;/code&gt;
 &lt;/pre&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The sender will:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Receiver CLI Reference</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/cli-reference/receiver/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/cli-reference/receiver/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="receiver-cli-reference"&gt;Receiver CLI Reference &lt;a href="#receiver-cli-reference" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;cloud-share-receiver&lt;/code&gt; is the NuGet global tool that connects to a running sender via Dev Tunnel, displays the queue in a local web UI, and lets you download and verify items.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="synopsis"&gt;Synopsis &lt;a href="#synopsis" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;


 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock "&gt;
 &lt;pre id="281909a" class="language- "&gt;
 &lt;code&gt;cloud-share-receiver [options]&lt;/code&gt;
 &lt;/pre&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="flags"&gt;Flags &lt;a href="#flags" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;table&gt;
 &lt;thead&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Flag&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Short&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Default&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Description&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/thead&gt;
 &lt;tbody&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;--port&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;-p&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;5001&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;The local port for the receiver&amp;rsquo;s web server&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;--log&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;-l&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;warnings&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Log level: &lt;code&gt;verbose&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;warnings&lt;/code&gt;, or &lt;code&gt;errors&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;--url&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;-u&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;em&gt;(prompted)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;The sender&amp;rsquo;s Dev Tunnel URL&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;--secret&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;-s&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;em&gt;(prompted)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;The session secret token from the sender&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;--no-prompt&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Skip the interactive prompt; requires &lt;code&gt;--url&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;--secret&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;--no-auto-open&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Do not open the web UI in the browser on startup&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;--help&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;-h&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Show help text&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;--version&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Show the tool version&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="flag-details"&gt;Flag details &lt;a href="#flag-details" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="--port---p"&gt;&lt;code&gt;--port&lt;/code&gt; / &lt;code&gt;-p&lt;/code&gt; &lt;a href="#--port---p" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Sets the local TCP port for the receiver&amp;rsquo;s HTTP server.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Security Best Practices</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/security/best-practices/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/security/best-practices/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="security-best-practices"&gt;Security Best Practices &lt;a href="#security-best-practices" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Cloud Share is designed to be secure by default, but the security of any transfer ultimately depends on how you use it. Follow these practices to ensure your transfers remain private and tamper-proof.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="use-cloudshare_secret-to-avoid-exposing-the-secret-in-the-process-list"&gt;Use &lt;code&gt;CLOUDSHARE_SECRET&lt;/code&gt; to avoid exposing the secret in the process list &lt;a href="#use-cloudshare_secret-to-avoid-exposing-the-secret-in-the-process-list" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Passing the secret as a &lt;code&gt;--secret&lt;/code&gt; flag puts it in your shell history &lt;strong&gt;and&lt;/strong&gt; the process argument list visible to &lt;code&gt;ps aux&lt;/code&gt; on the same machine. Use the &lt;code&gt;CLOUDSHARE_SECRET&lt;/code&gt; environment variable instead:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Core Concepts</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/getting-started/concepts/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/getting-started/concepts/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="core-concepts"&gt;Core Concepts &lt;a href="#core-concepts" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Before diving into advanced features, it helps to understand the building blocks that make cloud-share work. This page explains each concept at a level that will inform how you use the tool day-to-day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="dev-tunnels"&gt;Dev Tunnels &lt;a href="#dev-tunnels" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;Microsoft Dev Tunnel&lt;/strong&gt; is an outbound HTTPS connection from the sender machine to Microsoft&amp;rsquo;s relay infrastructure. It creates a publicly accessible URL (e.g. &lt;code&gt;https://abc123.devtunnels.ms&lt;/code&gt;) that proxies all requests back to the sender&amp;rsquo;s local port 5000.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Security Features</title><link>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/security/security-features/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://cloud-share-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/security/security-features/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="security-features"&gt;Security Features &lt;a href="#security-features" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;This page catalogues every security control implemented in cloud-share. Each control lists its industry-standard framework reference, the component it applies to, and the threat it addresses.&lt;/p&gt;
